This paper proposes a method for automatically designing the structure of layers in a feed-forward network, which is a common task in machine learning and specifically in deep learning. The paper discusses the trade-off between having too few or too many neurons in a network, which is a key concern in designing neural networks. The paper also presents results on image and non-image datasets, which suggests that the proposed method is effective. Given these factors, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
